e\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 107-member governing body of the biennial, biseasonal worldwide tournament conducted its vote after discussion and statements from individual members - mostly centering on anti-doping efforts in the wake of revelations that nearly two dozen swimmers had tested positive for a banned substance before the Tokyo Games - and were stillallowed to compete without ramifications.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the members commended Utah on its dedication to anti-performance-enhancing drug efforts during their comments.\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999893984654945, \"rank\": 1.0601108141083908e-05, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another theme among their comments was Utah's readiness to host a second event.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999893984654945, \"rank\": 1.0601108141083908e-05, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Members of the International Olympic Committee came to Salt Lake City in April for an up-close inspection of its venues and infrastructure to determine if it was, as Utah Lt. Gov.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://